                "Write this sentence ten times: 'Fermentation makes zero ATP. Glycolysis makes 2 ATP. Fermentation exists so glycolysis can keep running.' Do not proceed until this is automatic.",
                "Draw the two fermentation pathways as two parallel columns: alcoholic (pyruvate → acetaldehyde → ethanol + CO2) and lactic acid (pyruvate → lactate). Use one colour for CO2 appearing in alcoholic only. The visual separation immediately answers the CO2 question.",
                "Use the 'battery recharging' analogy for NAD+: glycolysis discharges the battery (NAD+ → NADH); fermentation recharges it (NADH → NAD+). Draw a battery icon at every stage of both pathways.",
                "List three organisms that do lactic acid fermentation (Lactobacillus, muscle cells, red blood cells) and three that do alcoholic fermentation (Saccharomyces, Zymomonas, some bacteria). Return to this list whenever confusion arises about which organisms do which."
