                energetics:  "Explain why the net ATP yield of glycolysis is 2 and not 4. Your explanation must distinguish gross yield from net yield and identify exactly which steps consume and which produce ATP.",
                regulation:  "Explain why PFK-1 is the primary regulatory enzyme of glycolysis rather than hexokinase, even though hexokinase catalyses the first step. Your answer must reference the concept of the committed step.",
                products:    "Explain why fermentation does not produce additional ATP, yet is essential for anaerobic survival. Your explanation must reference the role of NAD⁺ in step 6 and what would happen to glycolysis without fermentation.",
                context:     "Explain the Warburg effect. Your answer must state what makes it paradoxical (aerobic glycolysis) and propose why cancer cells might benefit from generating lactate even in the presence of oxygen."
